parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key independently moves in the ignition switch
the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the vehicle cannot be restarted
the dashboard lights and gauges shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause various safety-critical systems to fail, such as the steering, brakes, and airbags, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The sliding doors open and close by themselves
the rear hatch opens and closes by itself
the car alarm activates by itself
the windshield wipers turn on
various service lights illuminate on the dashboard
the speedometer and fuel gauge display improper readings
the windows do not function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause a fire, resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle engine bursts into flames
the front windshield explodes
a cloud of smoke appears
and huge flames come out of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Lift Gate Warning Alarm Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lift gate warning alarm can cause injuries or fatalities if the lift gate closes unexpectedly.
symptoms: The rear lift gate warning alarm does not sound when the lift gate is opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling or shut-off of the engine while driving can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
often while driving at various speeds
including low speeds
and may be accompanied by a loss of power
lights
and other functions. The vehicle may be difficult or impossible to restart
and may require towing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes running very hot
pulsating
and locking up; vehicle shaking when applying brakes; front and rear rotors warping or needing replacement at low mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or stranding the driver, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or shutting off without warning; intermittent issues with windows opening by themselves when the vehicle is turned off; tire pressure monitor system malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of brake components can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Front and rear brakes needing replacement at low mileage; factory rotors being too thin to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a warning alarm or alert when the rear lift gate is opening or closing can cause injuries to individuals walking around the vehicle, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The rear lift gate opens or closes without warning
causing individuals to walk into the edge of the gate
resulting in injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An unsecured luggage rack on top of the vehicle can fracture and detach while driving, causing damage to the vehicle and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The luggage rack on top of the vehicle is not securely fastened
and may fracture or detach while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An unhinged rear window can cause safety risks to occupants, especially children in car seats, and may lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear window becomes unhinged and hangs loose
causing a safety hazard.
